ply that such persons are disabled as a whole, equate persons with their condition, or have negative overtones of a derogatory or demeaning effect; and WHEREAS, the Legislature finds it important and appropriate to clarify that for new and revised laws and rules use should be made of terminology that puts the person before the disability: NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED, by the House of Representatives of the Eighty- second Legislature of the State of South Dakota, the Senate concurring therein, that the South Dakota Legislature will support language to put people first when referring to persons with disabilities in its statutes and rules."}, {"bill_id": 21704, "bill_version_id": 112521, "bill_version": "Enrolled", "bill_version_date": "2007-02-21T08:38:31-06:00", "bill_text": ""}], "amendments": [], "fiscal_notes": [], "action_log": [{"bill_id": 21704, "action_date": "2007-02-13T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 112207, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/112207.pdf", "status_text": "Introduced", "journal_page": 485, "committee_id_action": 923, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "N", "vote": {}}, {"bill_id": 21704, "action_date": "2007-02-14T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 112304, "document_url": "https://mylrc.sdlegislature.gov/api/Documents/112304.pdf", "status_text": "Adopt Resolution", "journal_page": 521, "committee_id_action": 923, "committee_id_assigned": null, "result": "P", "vote": {"vote_id": 67122, "president_vote": null, "Yea": [3572, 3576, 3577, 3578, 3579, 3580, 3581, 3582, 3583, 3586, 3587, 3588, 3590, 3591, 3592, 3593, 3594, 3597, 3598, 3599, 3600, 3604, 3605, 3606, 3609, 3611, 3613, 3614, 3616, 3619, 3620, 3622, 3624, 3628, 3629, 3631, 3632, 3635, 3637, 3638, 3640, 3642, 3643, 3644, 3645, 3646, 3648, 3649, 3650, 3651, 3653, 3654, 3655, 3656, 3657, 3658, 3660, 3662, 3663, 3665, 3666, 3668, 3670, 3671, 3672, 3673, 3674, 3675, 3676, 3584]}}, {"bill_id": 21704, "action_date": "2007-02-15T14:00:00-06:00", "document_id": 112